# ExceptionLib v0.1.1

ExceptionLib is a module designed to help make custom exceptions without having to create a new class.  
To install ExceptionLib, run the following command in your terminal:  
~~~Bash
pip install exceptionlib
~~~
Here are some examples of what you can do:
~~~Python
import exceptionlib
error = exceptionlib.CustomException(error="hello world!", error_type="HelloWorldError", traceback_code="raise CustomException(...)", traceback_file="...")

raise error
~~~
This will output:  
~~~Plaintext
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "...", line 108, in <module>
    raise CustomException(...)
    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
HelloWorldError: hello world!
~~~
